## Architecture

```
packages/shared    → IPC contracts, types, Zod schemas. No React, no Node.
packages/ui        → React component library (@ajh/ui). No app logic.
packages/prompts   → AI prompt templates. Pure TS, zero deps.
packages/core/ai/data/workers → Backend (main process) only. Never import in renderer.
apps/desktop/src/renderer     → React UI. No Node.js access.
```

The renderer communicates with main ONLY via `window.api.*` (IPC bridge).

---

## Rules — enforced by ESLint + TypeScript (violations fail CI)

### 1. Never call window.api in UI files — use service hooks
```ts
// ❌
const data = await window.api.documents.list();

// ✅
import { useDocuments } from '@/services';
const { data, isLoading } = useDocuments();
```

### 2. Import useTranslation from the adapter
```ts
// ❌
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

// ✅
import { useTranslation } from '@/lib/i18n';
```

### 3. Import UI components from @ajh/ui — never from deep local paths
```ts
// ❌
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { ButtonProps } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// ✅
import { Button } from '@ajh/ui';
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
```

The `apps/desktop/src/renderer/components/ui/` directory contains only legacy
re-export shims and `UpdateBanner` (app-specific). Do not add new files there.
All shared UI lives in `packages/ui` and is consumed via `@ajh/ui`.

### 4. Prefer inferred types over importing named component types
```ts
// ✅ Preferred
type MyProps = React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>;

// ✅ OK when extending
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
interface MyButtonProps extends ButtonProps { extra: string; }

// ❌ Avoid — no benefit over ComponentProps
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
const fn = (p: ButtonProps) => {};
```

Only import named types from `@ajh/ui` for non-obvious types: `ToastVariant`, `ThemeId`, `ToastItem`.

### 5. Import ordering (auto-fixable via `pnpm lint:fix`)
```ts
// 1. Node built-ins
// 2. External packages
// 3. @ajh/* packages
// 4. @/ aliases
// 5. Relative imports
```

### 6. Always use `import type` for type-only imports
```ts
// ❌
import { SomeType } from './types';

// ✅
import type { SomeType } from './types';
```

### 7. Use motion tokens — never inline transition objects
```ts
// ❌
transition={{ duration: 0.18, ease: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] }}

// ✅
import { transition } from '@/lib/motion';
transition={transition.normal}
```

### 8. Use brand tokens — never hardcode colors
```tsx
// ❌
className="text-[#c084fc] bg-[#a855f7]/15"

// ✅
className="text-brand-soft bg-brand/15"
```

### 9. Use shared UI primitives — never raw HTML for interactive elements
```tsx
// ❌
<button> <select> <textarea>

// ✅
import { Button, SelectDropdown, TextArea } from '@ajh/ui';
```
Allowed raw exceptions: `<input type="range|file|checkbox|radio|hidden">`.

### 10. Data fetching — React Query only
No `useState + useEffect` for remote data. Every IPC call has a service hook.

### 11. Main-process packages are forbidden in renderer
```ts
// ❌ in any renderer file
import { something } from '@ajh/core';
import { something } from '@ajh/data';
```

### 12. File placement
```
features/X/components/   → owned by one route only
components/layout/       → app chrome (Sidebar, Titlebar, PageShell)
services/                → all IPC + React Query hooks
lib/machines/            → state machine definitions (useMachine)
```
Features must not import from each other's internal directories.

### 13. New IPC capability checklist
1. `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts` — add signature
2. `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc/router.ts` — implement
3. `apps/desktop/src/preload/index.ts` — expose
4. `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/` — create hook

